      <div class="msgContentFrame">For most completed armor pieces, you usually need sinew cord (mole, antelope, etc.) or leather straps (sheep, dodo, etc.).  Some pieces require bolts of cloth, and a few require full pieces of cloth armor (hempen tabard -&gt; bronze chainmail, cotton tabard -&gt; sentinel's chainmail).  Other pieces require full pieces of leather to make. <br /> <br />I have weaver and tanner leveled to support my current needs, but by the time you reach rank 20-25 armorer, keeping up with the demands for materials from other classes on your own becomes quite a chore.  It's hard enough keeping myself supplied with shards just to skill up armorer.  Weaver tends to use the same kinds of shards (primarily earth and wind) which makes ranking up both classes simultaneously quite demanding.  There's also a time aspect.  I'm to the point now where I'm earning 200-300 skill points/synth on materials that are risky but mostly doable, and to get from rank 24 -&gt; 25 I need 28000 skill points.  That's an awful lot of iron rings, believe me.</div>
