      <div class="msgContentFrame">What aurelius said: Cloth, strap, some leather.  <br />Best way for you to know would be to take the armorer list of items (use yellow goblin for example) and note what is needed from leather/cloth. <br />I don't plan to level cloth myself, still considering leather as it comes in handy for some craft (not only for mats, but for some recipies too) to supplement my gold/smith/armor...  <br />Shard-wise it is really getting tough, burned about 1500 earth shard yesterday (but did 2 haubergeon at the end of the day so I'm happy). <br />wind shard I just cant find any decently priced (decent = 200/pop, maybe 250 max) so I mine them (but its slow). Earth are easy enough to farm, but while you farm, you dont craft... <br /> <br />On a related rant, I would like melee to realize that their repairs are costly. Just putting a 2000 or 3000 price tag wont cut it sometimes (and then hearing their complain really is annoying). <br />Example from this morning: Bronze plata (lvl 19 bronze based shield) = repair ingredient : bronze plate. Offered price : 5000. I was cool, lets do it... did it and made calculation afterwards... <br /> <br />tin ore -&gt; 500  <br />copper ore -&gt; lets say 333 x3 = 1000 <br />fire cristal -&gt; 2000 (cant find any cheaper than that, ever) <br />total 3500 for 12 nuggets, so 300/nuggets <br /> <br />5 nuggets + 8 fire shards (fire shard = 200/pop) -&gt; already 3100 to reach the ingot stage <br />add 8 earth shard ( 1000 for 8 shards, may be possible to buy some earth shard at 125/pop, not easy though) -&gt; 4100 to reach the ingredient you need to make the repair, of which only 600 are mats and 3500 are shards/cristal (pro-rata done). <br /> <br />this is without accounting for breaks (you can botch the repair at the end too, and have to pay everything again !) or time spent. <br /> <br />Basically melee should either lower their shard price (they are all happy to charge 300+/wind shard and 200 for each fire) or raise their repair prices. Otherwise they will go naked for all I care now. <br /> <br />Bottom line, as a crafter, really mind the shard cost, this is what will make or break you. <br />sometimes, guy brings me the (non processed) mats along with their repair and after I use 20 shards to do the necessary (along with my time) they think I should stop there, because they brought the mats and shards are &quot;easy to get&quot;... <br /> <br />shards are easy to get yes, but not in the huge quantities that are needed for any decent crafter. <br /> <br />Soon I will ask payment in shard only... <br />I would trade a hauby for 500 wind shard honestly. I dont do it because it takes 2 slot in my bazar (and immobilize 500 wind shard, that I dont have anymore anyway) and because a potential buyer may not have 500 shards on him either (but would have the 100k cheap money). Basically gils are kinda useless atm, everybody has tons. The real money is shard (much as real money isn't USD atm, but gold lol).  <br /> <br />Shards are money, shards are POWER ! :D <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /></div>
